            <text>
                <body>
                    <div xml:lang="nl" type="original">
<pb f="1r" n="1" xml:id="pb-orig-1r-1" facs="#zone-pb-1r-1"/><lb n="1" xml:id="l-1"/>

<p xml:id="p.orig.1" n="1">Amice Rappard</p><lb n="2" xml:id="l-2"/>

<p xml:id="p.orig.2" n="2">Uw schrijven ontving <lb n="3" xml:id="l-3"/>ik zooeven – tot mijn verwondering<c type="kp">.</c>– <lb n="4" xml:id="l-4"/>Ge ontvangt het hierbij terug<c type="kp">.</c>–<ptr target="#note-t-1"/></p><lb n="5" xml:id="l-5"/>

<p rend="indent" xml:id="p.orig.3" n="3">Na groete</p>
<space unit="lines" quantity="1"/><lb n="6" xml:id="l-6"/>

<p xml:id="p.orig.4" n="4">Vincent</p>
<space unit="lines" quantity="1"/></div>

                    <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                        <pb f="1r" n="1" xml:id="pb-trans-1r-1" facs="#zone-pb-1r-1"/>
<p xml:id="p.trans.1" n="1">My dear friend <rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_1306">Rappard</rs></p>
<p xml:id="p.trans.2" n="2">I just received your letter — to my surprise. You hereby get it back.<ptr target="#note-t-1"/></p>
<p rend="indent" xml:id="p.trans.3" n="3">Sincerely,</p><space unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
<p xml:id="p.trans.4" n="4">Vincent</p>
                    </div>
                </body>
            </text>
            <standOff>
                <listAnnotation xml:lang="en" type="typednotes">
                    
                    	<note xml:id="n_transcrSource" type="transcrSource">
                    	    
<p>Original manuscript</p>
                    	</note>
                    
                    
                    	<note xml:id="n_dating" type="dating">
                    	    
<p>Van Gogh wrote his terse note actually on Van Rappard’s letter of 24 May <ref target="let503.xml">(503)</ref>, which he had ‘just’ received. This means that in all likelihood his reply was written one day later than the letter, which is why we have dated it Monday, 25 May 1885. </p>
                    	</note>
                    
                    
                    
                </listAnnotation>
                <listAnnotation xml:lang="en" type="ogtnotes">
                    
                </listAnnotation>
                <listAnnotation xml:lang="en" type="notes">
                    
                        <note n="1" xml:id="note-t-1">
                            

<p>Van Gogh was very put out by <rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_1306">Van Rappard</rs>’s criticism in response to the lithograph of <hi rend="italics"><rs type="artwork" ref="artwork.xml#ill_2135">The potato eaters</rs></hi>. Returning a letter in this way was tantamount to ending the relationship. Van Gogh explained himself in more detail in <ref target="let514.xml">letter 514</ref>.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                            

                        
                    
